<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-19177] SAI query timeouts can cause resource leaks</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19177</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are several places in the SAI query path where a query timeout can result in a resource not being closed correctly. We need to make sure that wherever QueryContext.checkpoint is called we catch the resulting exception and close any open resources.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
